The paper deals with algorithms for predecessor/successor search, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. The focus is on static sets, which suggests a category related to data structures. The paper also mentions that the time bounds depend on different kinds of distance, which suggests categories related to information retrieval (IR) and databases (DB). The use of a finger to improve the running time suggests a category related to computational complexity (CC), while the use of global notions of distance suggests a category related to discrete mathematics (DM).
